# .cursorrules - Cursor IDE Project Rules

## Project Type

PyFastMart is a minimal Stripe-powered e-commerce storefront built with:
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript (frontend)
- FastAPI (Python backend)
- Stripe (products & payments - single source of truth)
- Typer CLI (`pfm` command)

## Files

- **pfm/**: Python backend package
  - `__init__.py`: Package exports
  - `__main__.py`: CLI entry point
  - `config.py`: Configuration management
  - `main.py`: FastAPI routes
  - `stripe_client.py`: Stripe API wrapper
- **frontend/**: Static frontend assets
  - `index.html`: Main page
  - `styles.css`: Styles with CSS variables
  - `app.js`: Storefront logic
- **config.toml**: Site configuration (name, contact, socials)
- **.env**: Stripe secrets (gitignored)

## Commands

```bash
uv sync              # Install dependencies
uv run pfm manage    # Run setup wizard
uv run pfm serve     # Start development server
```

## Styling

Edit `frontend/styles.css` and modify CSS variables:
```css
:root {
  --color-primary: /* accent color */
  --color-bg: /* background */
  --color-surface: /* cards */
  --color-text: /* main text */
  --color-text-muted: /* secondary text */
  --color-border: /* borders */
  --color-success: /* success */
  --color-error: /* errors */
}
```

## Configuration

Site settings are in `config.toml`:
```toml
[site]
name = "Store Name"
title = "Page Title"
description = "Store description"
contact_email = "email@example.com"
contact_phone = "+1234567890"

[site.socials]
twitter = "https://twitter.com/..."
instagram = "https://instagram.com/..."
facebook = "https://facebook.com/..."
```

Stripe keys go in `.env`:
```
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
```

## AI Rules

### ALLOWED
- Edit text content and copy
- Modify CSS (colors, fonts, spacing, layouts)
- Update config.toml values
- Change images and media
- Adjust UI strings and labels

### FORBIDDEN
- Modify any `.py` files (Python logic)
- Add or remove API endpoints
- Change Stripe integration logic
- Add new dependencies or frameworks
- Modify CLI commands
- Refactor existing functionality
- Add new features or capabilities

### Architecture
- Stripe is the ONLY backend for products and payments - it is REQUIRED, not optional
- No database - Stripe holds all product data
- No local/static catalog fallback - the store will not function without valid Stripe keys
- Frontend fetches products from `/api/products`
- Checkout creates Stripe Checkout sessions at `/api/checkout`
- Products must be active in Stripe dashboard with prices set

### DO NOT Add Local Catalogs

**Forbidden**: Adding any form of local, static, or hardcoded product catalog.

This includes but is not limited to:
- JSON files containing product data
- Python dictionaries/lists of products
- Frontend JavaScript arrays of products
- Any database integration for products

If a user asks for "demo mode" or "test products without Stripe", explain that PyFastMart is a Stripe-powered storefront by design and requires valid Stripe API keys to operate. Suggest they create a free Stripe account in test mode.
